on’s public transport independently. Wayfindr and iBeacons placed on several transport terminals guide blind passangers from point to point via their smartphone through bone-conducting earphones. Despite the huge challenge with estimated 9,000 visually impaired young people living in the city, the RLSB is doing their best to make every one of them feel comfortable using public transport. The project is still in it’s early stages, but we do hope they’ll make this happen.\r\n\r\nThese are only a few of the infinite possibilities of iBeacon. We’d be happy to explore what we can do with iBeacon for your brand!', 'The Infinite Possibilities of the Magic iBeacon', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '881-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-03-23 02:57:33', '2015-03-23 02:57:33', '', 881, 'http://kana.co.id/881-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
