(924, 1, '2015-05-26 02:41:14', '2015-05-26 02:41:14', '[caption id="attachment_918" align="aligncenter" width="391"]<a href="http://kana.co.id/assets/uploads/2015/05/Vector-Flat-Ui-Kit-LargeView.png"><img class="wp-image-918" src="http://kana.co.id/assets/uploads/2015/05/Vector-Flat-Ui-Kit-LargeView-1024x763.png" alt="Image credit : eragonj.me" width="391" height="292" /></a> Image credit : eragonj.me[/caption]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">In Kana, we get this question quite often from prospective clients: What is User Interface? So, let us define it in a simple way. The user interface (UI) is everything designed into an information device with which a person may interact. It include the process of crafting a visual language and hierarchy that allows someone to use and engage an application.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">In case you already have a website or an application, it’s time to ask, is your UI application “friendly” enough? A great user interface must provide a user-friendly experience, allowing the user to use the software or hardware in a natural and intuitive way. It’s important because if your potential customers find your website to be too complicated to navigate or too confusing, then even the best product in the world could be left collecting dust on the Internet.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">In Kana, when we build a website or applications for our clients, we create UI with a balance of amazing looks and interactivity with ease of use and simple navigation. For us, the goal of user interface design is to make the user knew the purpose of the site; they found the information they were looking for; and they loved it so much that they alerted the masses through their social networks of the site (Hey @Andy!  Check out this awesome site that sold me men clothing and looked hip to the jive!).</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">If you want to create a website or applications, there are important trends in 2015 that you need to be aware.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>“Mobile-First" Will Replace "Mobile-Friendly”</strong></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_919" align="aligncenter" width="391"]<a href="http://kana.co.id/assets/uploads/2015/05/Screen-Shot-2015-04-07-at-2.20.01-AM-1.png"><img class="wp-image-919" src="http://kana.co.id/assets/uploads/2015/05/Screen-Shot-2015-04-07-at-2.20.01-AM-1.png" alt="Screen Shot 2015-04-07 at 2.20.01 AM (1)" width="391" height="367" /></a> Image credit: inm.com[/caption]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Mobile is not a trend, nor is it even the future, it’s the present. We heard a lot about the importance of having a responsive or "mobile-friendly" website, however in 2015 we’ll see a shift into "mobile-first" mentality. If users find the UI is easy to use on mobile devices, they’ll be much happier with the app or the website.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Make It Big</strong><strong>ger</strong></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_920" align="aligncenter" width="400"]<a href="http://kana.co.id/assets/uploads/2015/05/Big_Really_Big.jpg"><img class="wp-image-920" src="http://kana.co.id/assets/uploads/2015/05/Big_Really_Big-300x150.jpg" alt="Big_Really_Big" width="400" height="201" /></a> Image credit : borngroup.com[/caption]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Have you noticed? Images are getting bigger. Nowadays, more and more designers are using full screen images and larger body images in their designs. This trend appears mostly in desktop designs. Nonetheless, in the last year this trend is showing up more and more on mobile as well.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Infographics Are Dead. Long Live Webgraphics</strong></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_921" align="aligncenter" width="391"]<a href="http://kana.co.id/assets/uploads/2015/05/sample-webgraphic.png"><img class="wp-image-921" src="http://kana.co.id/assets/uploads/2015/05/sample-webgraphic.png" alt="sample-webgraphic" width="391" height="245" /></a> Image credit : venturebeat.com[/caption]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">In the world of digital publishing, infographics have been the trend for the past few years and have become an outdated method of data visualization. However, with more and more users accessing content on their mobile devices, infographics need to grow beyond a static image and being replaced with Webgraphic which is more visually appealing and effective.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Video Backgrounds</strong></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_922" align="aligncenter" width="391"]<a href="http://kana.co.id/assets/uploads/2015/05/Nike-Website-600x300.jpg"><img class="wp-image-922" src="http://kana.co.id/assets/uploads/2015/05/Nike-Website-600x300-300x150.jpg" alt="Nike-Website-600x300" width="391" height="196" /></a> Image credit: nike.com[/caption]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">While video backgrounds are something we don’t see on mobile (because of technical restraints and bandwidth considerations), this rather new trend is great in the world of desktop. Stunning and engaging video backgrounds add motion and personality to a layout.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">You can be sure to see more of these trends in 2015. Try it on your next UI design project, and remember that User Interface is also the face of your brand!</p>\r\n&nbsp;', 'User Interface Design, Trends and Why Great UI Matters', 'In Kana, we get this question quite often from prospective clients: What is User Interface? So, let us define it in a simple way. The user interface (UI) is everything designed into an information device with which a person may interact. ', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '903-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-05-26 02:41:14', '2015-05-26 02:41:14', '', 903, 'http://kana.co.id/903-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(927, 1, '2015-06-19 05:57:37', '2015-06-19 05:57:37', 'Recently, we’ve seen more than a few crowdfunding campaigns spring up all over the net, some really effective ones also. The idea of crowdfunding or the act of reaching out to individual people to raise money is actually anything but new. What is new though, is the way the money is being raised. Thanks to the internet and social media, it’s becoming increasingly easier to find and connect with other people who share the same passion. The crowdfund itself is an individual or a group that comes forward with a plan for a project they wish to fund, and look to a group of people who actually provide the money to support the development and the delivery of the project.\r\n\r\n<strong>So, why is crowdfunding a good idea?</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://kana.co.id/assets/uploads/2015/06/Crowdfunding-2-of-1.jpg"><img class=" wp-image-928 alignleft" src="http://kana.co.id/assets/uploads/2015/06/Crowdfunding-2-of-1-300x200.jpg" alt="Crowdfunding-2-of-1" width="218" height="145" /></a>\r\n\r\nLots of people have good ideas, and we believe that the internet should be used to help people out and give a real voice to the voiceless. Crowdfunding allows people to reach their goals, and allows folks contribute to causes they believe in. Crowdfunding is a great alternative way to fund a project, and it can be done without giving up equity or accumulating debt. Rewards-based crowdfunding platforms let entrepreneurs raise funds from the community in exchange for simply providing tangible products or other relative gifts.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAn active crowdfunding campaign is a good way to introduce a venture’s overall mission and vision to the market, as it is a free and simple way to reach numerous channels. A lot of crowdfunding platforms incorporate social media mechanisms, making it easy to get traffic to your website and other social media pages. Typically, this allows ventures to receive thousands of organic visits from unique users and potential funders. These users are also key for viral marketing, as they have the potential to share and spread the word to their connections.\r\n\r\n<strong>How about the story of crowdfunding in Indonesia?</strong>\r\n\r\nCan crowdfunding find success in Indonesia? Indonesians are familiar with the “gotong royong” principle. Gotong royong itself means working together as a community, a principle starting to move to the digital world. In 2012, we saw some big headlines for Indonesia’s crowdfunding scene.\r\n\r\nThe most successful funding was for “Atambua 39º Celcius”, a movie directed by Indonesian writer and director, Mira Lesmana. Posted in Wujudkan.com, an Indonesian crowdfunding site, the project collected more than the Rp 300 million (approximately $31,071). Another movie that was successfully funded by the public in 2012 was Demi Ucok, a movie, which screened in Indonesian cinemas in January 2013. After seven months of self-organized crowdfunding, Demi Ucok successfully gathered Rp 250 million.\r\n\r\nCrowdfunding also has a big role in the gaming industry.  A developer from Bandung  gathered Rp 585,5 million (or USD 48.000) in Kickstarter to create his new game, Pale Blue,  which started from May 12<sup>th</sup>, 2014 until June 20, 2014.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://kana.co.id/assets/uploads/2015/06/pale_blue_by_sinlaire-d70kt43.jpg"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-932" src="http://kana.co.id/assets/uploads/2015/06/pale_blue_by_sinlaire-d70kt43-300x163.jpg" alt="pale_blue_by_sinlaire-d70kt43" width="230" height="125" /></a>\r\n\r\nPale Blue actually exceeded its requested amount, raking in Rp 727,1 million (or USD 59.574). With those numbers, Pale blue became the most successful crowdfunded game in the Indonesian game industry until now. Does this mean that the Indonesian crowdfunding industry has finally made it? To answer this question, you could take a look at four popular Indonesian crowdfunding sites: Wujudkan.com for creative industry, Kitabisa and Ayopeduli for social projects, and Mekar.biz for business projects.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHowever, being successful in crowdfunding is not as easy as it seems. It comes with efforts and dedication.', 'Exploring The Potential Power of Crowdfunding', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'exploring-the-potential-power-of-crowdfunding', '', '', '2015-06-19 06:08:08', '2015-06-19 06:08:08', '', 0, 'http://kana.co.id/?p=927', 0, 'post', '', 0),
